526
00:21:16.927 --> 00:21:19.974
Her parents thought she was
in D.C. visiting a friend.

527
00:21:20.148 --> 00:21:21.976
♪ ♪

528
00:21:22.106 --> 00:21:26.372
Car had no plates.
Bag full of cash.

529
00:21:26.502 --> 00:21:29.288
Lauren was running.

530
00:21:29.418 --> 00:21:32.987
She was afraid for her life.
and Carrie warned me.

531
00:21:33.161 --> 00:21:34.902
♪ ♪

532
00:21:35.032 --> 00:21:37.992
And thanks to your client.
they're both dead.

533
00:21:38.166 --> 00:21:39.907
♪ ♪

534
00:21:40.037 --> 00:21:42.213
Normally. I'd be happy
to throw Tariq under the bus.

535
00:21:42.388 --> 00:21:43.998
♪ ♪

536
00:21:44.128 --> 00:21:47.306
Until today.
he had an ankle monitor.

537
00:21:47.436 --> 00:21:48.829
Did it go off last night?

538
00:21:49.003 --> 00:21:50.352
♪ ♪

539
00:21:50.439 --> 00:21:51.788
No.

540
00:21:51.919 --> 00:21:53.529
And thus far.

541
00:21:53.660 --> 00:21:55.444
evidence points to Carrie
committed suicide.

542
00:21:55.575 --> 00:21:57.490
Isn't that suspicious?

543
00:21:57.577 --> 00:21:59.927
It's too perfect
to actually be a suicide.

544
00:22:00.057 --> 00:22:02.973
Or a career-driven woman
overcome by her feelings

545
00:22:03.060 --> 00:22:06.673
of anger. guilt. shame
felt powerless

546
00:22:06.803 --> 00:22:09.371
